cs.SY, cs.RO, cs.LO, cs.MA, cs.PL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the synthesis of controllers for multi-agent dynamical systems. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also a likely category as the paper presents robotic experiments performed on a multi-robot testbed. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper uses linear temporal logic to specify task specifications. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is relevant as the paper deals with multi-agent systems. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the synthesis of control laws which could be seen as a programming task.
